---
const { class: className } = Astro.props;
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";
---

<div
  class:list={[
    "pattern py-6 w-full md:w-3/4 md:max-w-8xl min-h-dynamic_hero flex flex-col items-center justify-center",
    className,
  ]}
>
  <div class="flex flex-col-reverse md:flex-row">
    <div
      class="flex flex-col gap-4 md:w-1/2 p-8 justify-center items-center md:items-start"
    >
      <h1
        class="text-pretty text-center md:text-left md:text-4xl lg:text-5xl tracking-wide"
      >
        Welcome to <i class="text-primary">nixthe.systems</i>
      </h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-center md:text-left mt-4">
        A platform dedicated to sharing Nix configurations and building a thriving community.
      </p>
      <p class="text-lg text-center md:text-left mt-4">
        As a Nix enthusiast and university student, I'm committed to providing:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-lg text-center md:text-left mt-4">
        <li>🌐 Supporters will receive their own subdomain (e.g., john.nixthe.systems).</li>
        <li>🛠️ Curated configurations from Nix users, inspired by dotfyle.com.</li>
        <li>🤝 Free assistance in building your own Nix configurations.</li>
        <li>📚 Comprehensive documentation for modules like nix-darwin and Home Manager.</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-lg text-center md:text-left mt-4">
        I’m passionate about fostering a stronger community. If you're a designer, developer, or simply have insights to share, your input is invaluable—don’t hesitate to reach out or open an issue with your thoughts!
      </p>
      <a href="/getting-started" class="py-4">
        <Button size="lg" className="rounded-lg">
          <h4 class="text-lg">Get Started</h4>
        </Button>
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<style></style>
